'''''So Impossible EP''''' is [[Dashboard Confessional]]'s second EP. It was released on [[December 18]], [[2001]] through [[Vagrant Records]]. [[Chris Carrabba]], who was the only official member back then, solidified his stature as the leader of the [[Emo (music)|emo]]-revolution through the album.{{fact}} The EP release was also widely acclaimed and received great scores in music review magazines like [[Spin magazine|SPIN]]. All four songs would later be performed in Dashboard Confessional's [[MTV Unplugged 2.0|MTV Unplugged]] performance. The same performance was released as an album in [[2002 in music|2002]].
The EP is also notable as Carrabba's only recorded collaboration with former [[Sunny Day Real Estate]] guitarist [[Dan Hoerner]].
